In the following sections we present a possible indicator system of effectiveness and success using this second approach. This system of indicators formed the basis of the School questionnaire. When defining criteria, we differentiate between the criteria of success and effectiveness. According to our approach, the former reflects the school's performance, the result of its work. And the later serves as the extent of expenditure (financial, time, etc.) essential to obtain a result. The indexes of effectiveness are defined on the basis of educational activity and socialisation effectiveness of the school, and how well-known and recognised it is in its surroundings. These indexes were defined mainly on the basis of a research made by the Research Centre of the National Institute of Public Education (Halász, 1996).
